NASCO Group has lent its voice to the fight against COVID 19 with the donation of products from the stable of the company worth over N20 million to Lagos state government. Speaking during the presentation of the products to the Lagos state government representatives in Ikeja, Rotimi Oyesiji, general manager, Marketing representing Dr Attia Nasreddin, executive chairman NASCO group said NASCO Group Nigeria is in many respects pleased to continue to be a part of the journey of Nigeria as a nation. He said “This pandemic offers us all a chance to engage our today and tomorrow with a different type of energy. Indeed, our economic and social life may never be the same again, but today, we have a definite choice to make: to become a more caring and engaged community, so that together, we shall always advocate for the realization of a better health care system, offering wider access to more of our people, ultimately”. The items comprised of top quality NASCO products, and are made up of: One trailer load of Action Detergent multipurpose, for hand washing, cleaning of surfaces and related hygiene practices in Lagos and Ogun States. One trailer load of NASCO Whole Flaked Cornflakes (to feed persons in COVID-19 isolation centres in Lagos and the Ogun States; to serve vulnerable and deserving communities including in Internally Displaced Peoples’ – IDP – camps). Accepting the presentation on behalf of Lagos state government, programme manager, Lagos state Ministry of Agric Development Authority, Dr Pereira Sheteolu expressed gratitude to the NASCO Group for joining the fight against COVID 19. 